\par \pard\plain \s21\loch\sl276\slmult1\sb0\sa140\ql\ltrpar{\loch
This document presents the construction of a fully extensible symbolic framework for Quantum Arithmetic (QA) in Common Lisp. Leveraging modular 4-tuples and harmonic algebra, the system includes components for theorem synthesis, Fourier decomposition, toroidal projection, post-quantum cryptography, and category-theoretic morphisms. It enables formal reasoning, simulation of harmonic fields, symbolic REPL interaction, and theorem verification infrastructure. The project demonstrates how QA logic supports both mathematical elegance and computational replicability, suggesting a new paradigm for symbolic mathematics.}
